div
	div.closePopUp(ng-click="closePopup()") X
	h3 Hey there. 
	p So far we've got: 
	p You: {{identity.currentUser.firstname}} {{identity.currentUser.lastname}}
	p The area and location: {{mapPoints.geometry.coordinates}}
	p The wildlife within the corridor: {{wildlife[0].name}}
	p And the types of monitors you're using: {{monitors}}
	p
	p But before we can begin we need to ask just a few more questions like:
	p What is name of the project? <br>
		input(type="text" ng-model="projectName")
	p How would you describe the project? <br>
		textarea(cols="30" rows="10" ng-model="projectDescription")
	p The project start and end dates: <br>
		input(type="date" ng-model="start_date") 
		input(type="date" ng-model="end_date")
	p Is this a private, public or government project 
		select(class="form-control" ng-model="orgs.type", ng-options="org.value as org.name for org in selectOrg")
	p What is the required funding target? <br>
		input(type="number" min="0" value="0" ng-model="fundingRequired")
	p An image

	p Finally would you like to invite anyone?

	div
		b(class="popupCancel" ng-click="cancelProject()") Clear
		b(class="popupSave" ng-click="saveProject(projectName, projectDescription, start_date, end_date, orgs.type, fundingRequired); projectPopup('hide');") Save